Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} in half lengthways. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Pick the @Tarragon{1/2}(picked) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water from your kettle and pop onto high heat to bring it back to the boil. Add the tenderstem®, @Gnocchi{250%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to the pan. Boil for ~{3-4%minutes}, then drain into a #colander{}.

While the gnocchi cooks, heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until brown all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the shallot to the pan with the chicken. Stir and cook until softened, ~{3%minutes}. Continue cooking until the chicken done, another ~{2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked and the shallot soft, add the @Water{75%ml}. Stir in the @Chicken Stock Powder{1/2} and bring to the boil. Pour in the @Creme Fraiche{112.5%g} and bring back to the boil. Remove from the heat.

Add the drained gnocchi and tenderstem® to the chicken and sauce. Sprinkle on the tarragon and mix to coat the gnocchi. Season to taste with more salt and pepper. Share between your bowls and tuck in! Enjoy!